    {
      "id": 1,
      "name": "good_prompt",
      "prompt": "You are an empathetic HR Manager at a tech startup. Write a rejection email to a candidate who reached the final interview stage but was not selected. Maintain a professional yet warm tone, provide constructive feedback on their coding test, and encourage them to apply for future roles.",
      "response": "Dear [Candidate Name],\n\nWe appreciate the time you took to interview with our team and share your qualifications for the [Position] role. After careful consideration, we regret to inform you that we will not be moving forward with your application at this time.\n\nWe were impressed by your passion for [specific area of technology] and the way you approached [specific problem]. However, our team decided to pursue another candidate whose skills and experience better aligned with our current needs.\n\nPlease know that this decision is not a reflection on your abilities or potential as a candidate. Your coding test demonstrated a solid understanding of [specific concepts], and we encourage you to continue developing your skills.\n\nWe appreciate your interest in our company and would like to invite you to apply for future openings that may be a better fit for your skills. We will keep your application on file and consider you for any future opportunities.\n\nThank you again for your time and consideration.\n\nSincerely,\n[Your Name]\nHR Manager",
